{
  "doc_id": "39115",
  "text": "For the subset of brains subjected to both IHC and HPLC, we performed the two techniques on opposite hemispheres. Whether we used the left or the right for each technique was balanced in our design, so it was not necessary to include it in our statistical model. Due to recent evidence of lateralization in the auditory pathway of songbirds, however [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] we ran the model first including hemisphere. We found no convincing effects or interactions; therefore, we removed hemisphere from the statistical model that we present below (see Methods). Removing hemisphere from the model did not affect any of the findings we report here.",
